---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Why Stainless Steel Wire Pegs Are Worth It"
  description="Discover why stainless steel wire pegs outlast plastic and wooden pegs, save you money, and are better for the environment. The complete guide."
>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="py-24 px-6 bg-stone-50">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-400 mb-4">The Case For Wire Pegs</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-stone-800 leading-tight mb-6">
        Why Stainless Steel Wire Pegs Are Worth It
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-stone-500 leading-relaxed">
        Most people buy cheap pegs without thinking about it. Then they buy them again. And again. Here's why wire pegs are the last pegs you'll ever need.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CONTENT -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto prose prose-stone prose-lg">

      <!-- Problem with plastic -->
      <div class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-stone-800 mb-6">The problem with plastic pegs</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Plastic clothes pegs are one of those products that seem cheap until you realise how often you replace them. The spring rusts. The plastic cracks in the sun. They stain your clothes. They snap in half on a windy day.</p>
        <p class="text-stone-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">The average Australian household buys a new pack of pegs every 1–2 years. Over a decade, that's 5–10 packs of pegs — most of which end up in landfill, because plastic pegs can't be recycled.</p>
        <p class="text-stone-600 leading-relaxed">And the irony? The cheap peg ends up being the expensive one.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Problem with wood -->
      <div class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-stone-800 mb-6">The problem with wooden pegs</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Wooden pegs feel like a sustainable alternative — but they have their own problems. Left outside, they absorb moisture, swell, crack, and eventually grow mould that transfers to your clean washing.</p>
        <p class="text-stone-600 leading-relaxed">The spring mechanism is still metal, still rusts, and still fails. Wooden pegs are better than plastic — but they're not the solution.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Why wire pegs -->
      <div class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-stone-800 mb-6">Why wire pegs are different</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Wire Pegs are made from a single continuous piece of stainless steel wire — bent into shape. There is no spring. There is no separate clip. There are no parts to fail.</p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 my-8">
          <div class="bg-stone-50 rounded-xl p-6">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-800 mb-2">✓ Never breaks</h3>
            <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm">No spring mechanism means nothing to snap or rust.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-stone-50 rounded-xl p-6">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-800 mb-2">✓ Won't stain clothes</h3>
            <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm">No rust transfer onto your clean white washing.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-stone-50 rounded-xl p-6">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-800 mb-2">✓ Cools quickly</h3>
            <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm">Metal conducts heat away fast — safe to handle even on hot days.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-stone-50 rounded-xl p-6">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-800 mb-2">✓ Multi-purpose</h3>
            <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm">Use as food bag clips, paper clips, garden ties, and more.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Cost comparison -->
      <div class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-stone-800 mb-6">The real cost comparison</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">Wire pegs cost more upfront. But over time, they're significantly cheaper.</p>
        <div class="bg-stone-800 text-white rounded-2xl p-8">
          <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-4 text-center">
            <div>
              <p class="text-stone-400 text-xs uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Plastic Pegs</p>
              <p class="text-2xl font-bold mb-1">$50+</p>
              <p class="text-stone-400 text-sm">over 10 years</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-stone-400 text-xs uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Wooden Pegs</p>
              <p class="text-2xl font-bold mb-1">$40+</p>
              <p class="text-stone-400 text-sm">over 10 years</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white text-stone-800 rounded-xl p-4">
              <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Wire Pegs</p>
              <p class="text-2xl font-bold mb-1">~$20</p>
              <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm">once, forever</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Environment -->
      <div class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-stone-800 mb-6">Better for the environment</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Every broken plastic peg goes to landfill. It can't be recycled. It sits there for hundreds of years.</p>
        <p class="text-stone-600 leading-relaxed">A single set of Wire Pegs replaces dozens of packs of plastic pegs over a lifetime. That's a simple, meaningful swap that reduces your household plastic waste with zero lifestyle change required.</p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="bg-stone-800 text-white py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Ready to make the switch?</h2>
      <p class="text-stone-300 mb-8">Not sure which grade is right for you? Use our Peg Finder first.</p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/which-peg" class="bg-white text-stone-800 font-semibold px-8 py-4 rounded-full hover:bg-stone-100 transition-colors">
          Find My Peg →
        </a>
        <a href="https://www.biome.com.au/collections/wire-pegs" target="_blank" class="border border-stone-500 text-white font-semibold px-8 py-4 rounded-full hover:border-white transition-colors">
          Shop at Biome →
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>